    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hollandaise breaks when the emulsion of egg yolks and butter can no longer hold together, usually due to overheating the yolks or adding butter too quickly. You can often fix it by slowly whisking in a cool liquid like lemon juice or water to cool the mixture down, then gently re-emulsifying the butter over low heat. However, if the yolks cooked into scrambled eggs or the butter fully separated, it is likely ruined and best discarded. For your next attempt, keep the heat low and add the butter in a thin, steady stream while whisking constantly.",
